{
  "doc_id": "27140",
  "text": "We have little understanding as to why patients refuse a permanent access or even refuse to cannulate a viable fistula. Potential reasons could be related to quality of life and the possibility of undergoing unnecessary surgery [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Our group is currently researching this area to address these barriers to using a fistula.",
